A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to homeland security; amending a definition
2 to include certified water and wastewater operators for
3 purposes of emergency response; requiring local homeland
4 security plans to coordinate with certified water and
5 wastewater operators as specified; and providing for an
6 effective date.
7
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
9
10 Section 1. W.S. 19-13-108 and 35-9-152(a)(i) are
11 amended to read:
12
13 19-13-108. Local programs; authorized; local homeland
14 security plan; coordinators; appointment and removal.
15
1 HB0022

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0005
1 Each political subdivision of this state shall establish a
2 local homeland security program in accordance with the
3 state homeland security plan and program. Each political
4 subdivision through the homeland security program will
5 cause to be prepared a local homeland security plan which
6 will include actions essential to the recovery and
7 restoration of the economy by supply and resupply of
8 resources to meet urgent survival and military needs and to
9 provide for the ongoing management of resources available
10 to meet continuing survival and recovery needs. Each local
11 homeland security plan shall require coordination with each
12 certified water and wastewater operator necessary to
13 provide emergency and public safety services for homeland
14 security. Each local homeland security program shall have a
15 coordinator appointed by the governor upon the
16 recommendation of the local jurisdiction. The coordinator
17 has direct responsibility for the organization,
18 administration and operation of the local homeland security
19 program subject to the direction and control of the local
20 jurisdiction under the general direction of the governor.
21 The governor may remove any coordinator as provided in W.S.
22 9-1-202.
23
