1 35-9-152. Definitions.
2
3 (a) As used in this act:
4
5 (i) "Emergency responders" means public, state
6 or federal fire services, law enforcement, emergency
7 medical services, public health, public works including
8 certified water and wastewater operators, homeland security
9 and other public response services or agencies that would
10 be involved in direct actions to contain or control a
11 hazardous material release, weapons of mass destruction
12 incident or clandestine laboratory investigation. The term
13 "emergency responders" does not include private on-site
14 facilities with immediate emergency response capabilities
15 unless formally requested to assist off the private
16 facility site by the state or a political subdivision of
17 the state;
